</relationEntry>
<descriptiveNote>
<p>The Royal Commission stimulated the government to implement the <span style="font-style:italic">Lunacy Act Amendment Act 1950</span>, which had a greater impact on adults than on children in the mental health system. The amendments defined the terms 'restraint' and 'seclusion' and enhanced the role and responsibilities of the Board of Visitors, who were expected to be able to provide the Minister with detailed information about the operation of the Act within the State's mental health institutions.</p>
</descriptiveNote>
